{"key":"post-11672293","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>11672293</id>\n<content>I've found coir to be the equal of manure when growing dung and straw loving species.&amp;nbsp; Shittake refuses to fruit on it at all.&amp;nbsp; Unless your spawn is contaminated, coir is good for a very long time.&amp;nbsp; In fact, you can wet coir down and toss it in a corner for months and it won't get moldy.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;I don't get involved in discussion of 'nutes', and I promise I wasn't singling you out(koopa).&amp;nbsp; If you look back six or seven years ago when I first started posting here, I brought the &lt;a href=&quot;/forums/showflat.php/Number/2521776#2521776&quot; class=&quot;pp&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;idea of coir as a substrate&lt;/a&gt; to the shroomery.&amp;nbsp; I got banned at the other mushroom site for spreading disinformation, by calling coir a good substrate material.&amp;nbsp; When I repeated the claims here, I didn't get banned, but sure got called a few other choice names before people started using it and found it works. &lt;img style=&quot;max-width:192px;height:auto;&quot; src=&quot;https://files.shroomery.org/smileys/laugh.gif&quot; alt=&quot;:laugh:&quot; title=&quot;:laugh:&quot;/&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The simple fact is, humans have been studying plants for thousands of years, but are just now beginning to learn about fungi.&amp;nbsp; I don't think anyone really knows what 'nutes' fungi requires.&amp;nbsp; We experiment with different substrates, repeating with ones that work, and pushing aside those which fail.&amp;nbsp; That's how we got to where we are today, and future generations will build on our work.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;I'm also working on a morel fruiting tek.&amp;nbsp; I suspect it has more to do with the strain than with ingredients in the substrate.&amp;nbsp; If you can find a spot where the morels pop every year regardless of whether there was a fire or other tree-kill event, that's the culture you want to work with.&amp;nbsp; I finally live in a spot where morels come up on my own property, so the race is on to find a way to cultivate them commercially.&amp;nbsp; If I can pull that off, I'll be a very rich rabbit.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>11672299</next>\n<prev>11672287</prev>\n<first>11666108</first>\n<last>11677542</last>\n<when>1261115400</when>\n<utime>12/18/09 07:50 AM</utime>\n</post>"}